    "mysticalOpening1": "The Cavapendoli descend in a spiral, almost swift.",
    "mysticalOpening2": "They were once everywhere, in the warehouses of the intangible world.",
    "mysticalOpening3": "Slowly, over time, they took shape.",
    "mysticalOpening4": "First images, then paintings, then words.",
    "mysticalOpening5": "But they didn't like to be fixed in place.",
    "mysticalOpening6": "As time passed, they accepted being exposed to the gaze of strangers.",
    "mysticalOpening7": "Now they hesitate, perhaps they don't want to be stopped on paper.",
    "mysticalOpening8": "They slip away, because they live in freedom.",
    "mysticalOpening9": "They are benign, hilarious, slippery and witty.",
    "mysticalOpening10": "They come and go, flutter about, land and leave.",
    "mysticalOpening11": "Who knows what they do when they're not showing themselves.",
    "mysticalOpening12": "I invite them with humility to enter the barrel of the pen...",
    "mysticalOpening13": "and they giggle at me."
